[+663] "100 Billion" The Most Profound Image in Human History
item.description: This is the deepest image yet of the Universe in near-infrared light. The faintest and reddest objects in the image are likely the oldest galaxies ever identified, having formed between only 600–900 million years after the Big Bang. The image shows thousands of galaxies, some more than 12 billion years old.

item.title: [+602] A 19th-Century Mathematician Finally Proves Himself
item.description: In the mid-1800s, Charles Babbage got fed up with doing complex calculations by hand, so he designed what he called a "Difference Engine." He never built the machine in his lifetime, but 150 years later, engineers built the engine to Babbage's specifications and the 5-ton calculator actually works.
